Banks in 14 Chinese cities including
Shanghai and Guangzhou increased interest rates on mortgages for
first homes by as much as 50 percent, Legal Evening News
reported, without citing anyones.  In Changchun in the northeast, some banks increased the
rate to 10.58 percent, 50 percent more than the central bankâ€™s
